added.title: A Rusty Rescue
added.description: When Thomas throws away Diesel's favorite oil can thinking it's trash, he makes a promise to get it back and learns it's better not to touch things that aren't yours.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Hide and Surprise!
added.description: While playing hide and seek with Percy, Diesel accidentally gets stranded on a barge that floats out to sea, where it becomes a group effort to rescue him.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Toy Party
added.description: Bing and Hoppity, Pando and Bullabaloo are all having a tea party at Sula and Hippoty's today! But what will happen when Sula gives Bullabaloo more cake than Hoppity, and Bing thinks that's not fair?

added.title: Cell Phone
added.description: Bing and Hoppity want to play with Talking Lettuce on Flops cell phone. Bing remembers to put the cell phone down when he wants to voosh with Hoppity. But what happens when Bing vooshes a little too close to Flop's cell phone?

added.title: Show
added.description: Bing and his friends are at the bandstand in the park when they all decide to put on a show! And Bing's singing the Rainybow song for the finale! But what will happen when Bing doesn't like everybody looking at him?

added.title: Pato's Egg
added.description: Pato finds an egg and immediately falls in love with it: he wants to take care of the little baby inside the egg. When the egg hatches he gets the shock of his life: it's not a cute little duckling at all, but a very odd looking spider. His friends are terrified of the little creature and won't play with Pato if he brings it along. Pato rather craftily and meanly makes the little spider go away and do things on its own, so Pato can play with Pocoyo and Elly. Finally the little spider makes their hearts melt when he shows them that there's nothing to be scared of and he just wants to be their friend.

added.title: Dance Off!
added.description: Pocoyo and Pato stumble upon a disco and Elly is the DJ. Pato gets grooving to a track and Elly thinks he's fantastic. But Pocoyo's not impressed. He has a go and shows his dance. It's wonderful, but then Pato thinks he can do even better. And so it goes on - an impromptu, ever-so-funky dance off! Things get out of hand when Pocoyo is raving and Pato is body-popping so Elly changes the record. She takes to the dance floor and shows the rivals - in an uncannily Britney-esque way - that instead of competing, they can all have fun dancing together! It's much more fun.

added.title: Get Lost Loula
added.description: Let's play Hide and Seek! Pocoyo is the seeker and is brilliant at it - but only thanks to Loula. When Loula gets all the praise for being a super-seeker, Pocoyo is jealous. He throws a ball very far away to make Loula run off and chase it. His friends think it was a nasty thing to do and so Pocoyo feels bad and decides he must now find Loula. They follow her footprints but she's gone really far and they just can't find her anywhere. Finally at an island in the sea they despair: they think she's gone forever. But we can already see that Loula is safe and sound. Everyone is reunited and Pocoyo can celebrate being a super-seeker too, after all.

added.title: Christmas Tree
added.description: It's Christmas time and Pato wants to decorate a Christmas tree. He can't bring himself to fell an innocent fern, but with a bit of ingenuity and a lot of team work the gang manages to find the perfect tree. Merry Christmas!

added.title: An Alien Christmas Carol
added.description: The angry Martian hates Christmas since his father disappeared one Christmas Eve and he's decided to use his cannon to ruin Christmas for Pocoyo and his friends. But you never know what life has in store. After all, everyone has a heart.

added.title: Fireworks
added.description: Bing is excited to watch the Fireworks outside, but will they be too noisy loud?

added.title: Bye Bye
added.description: Bing loves playing with his new orange balloon, but what will happen when he bounces on it too much?

added.title: Old Macdonald
added.description: Rishi goes around the farm with Ella, organising all the animals so they can have a soccer game!

added.title: Planets
added.description: Three, two, one, Blast Off! The BlippiMobile becomes a spacecraft on this mission to find out which planets are in the solar system! Merry the Meteor is the perfect host as Blippi is escorted through space and receives a guided tour of all the planets and their positions from the sun.

added.title: Shake the Apple Tree
added.description: It's the end of the summer and the trees are full of delicious apples ready to be picked!

added.title: Fruit & Vegetables
added.description: On the hunt to discover the difference between fruits and vegetables, Blippi finds himself as a contestant in a community garden game show! Game show host Slim Cucumber quizzes Blippi on his knowledge of fruits and vegetables. Will Blippi know the answers?

added.title: Boot Castle/Avocado's Long Time Out/Tanks Giving
added.description: Findley discovers a boot that him and Lucas use as a castle./ When they hear Avocado has been put in her naughty crate, Lucas and Findley entertain her./ Lucas brings Dimples things from around the house so she doesn't feel left out.

added.title: Flying/Dr. Lucas is in the House/Arlo's Portrait
added.description: After watching Findley in flight, Lucas wonders what it would be like to fly./ Dr. Lucas tries to make all his friends feel better but ends up under the weather himself./ Lucas decides to paint a portrait of Arlo. But Arlo can't sit still.

added.title: Good Vibrations
added.description: Lilit is under pressure. Truff, the most talented musician in Mushton, has invited her, Mush-Mush and Chep to form a band with him. Only problem is they can hardly play music! Truff insists: they just need to relax and feel the groove. But when Truff tells his new band they will perform at the Food Snail, Lilit isn't relaxed at all!

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: Chep knows so many things about nature that Mush-Mush and Lilit are confident he's not far from being an expert like Mushpot. So, when Travel Snail seems unwell, Mush-Mush and Lilit encourage their friend to take care of her in Mushpot's absence. Chep's diagnosis takes everyone by surprise: Travel Snail is expecting baby snails! At least that's what Chep is convinced about.

added.title: Out of the Cheer Zone
added.description: Two mischievous Whiffle kids come to play with Dibble, forcing Cheer to put her important work on hold to manage them. When she finds her "managing kids" skills lacking and her important work in jeopardy, she uses her skills as a leader to get the kids working as a team to help her complete her work while having fun at the same time.

added.title: The Last Laugh
added.description: Disappointed when his friends don't laugh at his jokes, Funshine encounters the Laffinpuff, a magical comedian who grants Funshine's wish to make everyone think he's funny. But Funshine realizes it's no fun being funny when people laugh at everything he says, whether he means it to be funny or not. To get the wish rescinded, he must face the Laffinpuff in a grueling ordeal of slapstick humor.

added.title: Move It!
added.description: Overhearing Granny making a call to Manny the Mover, Baby Bugs and Baby Lola jump to the conclusion they're all moving away from Granny's house.

added.title: The Neat and the Sloppy
added.description: A study in contrasts enlivens this odd couple's antics. Baby Daffy is the compulsive mess maker, and Baby Sylvester is the cleanliness freak.

added.title: Time Out!
added.description: Bugs, Daffy and Taz are disciplined by having a time out in the corner.

added.title: Present Tense
added.description: The Baby Looney Tunes pitch in to make an Arbor Day gift for Granny while Baby Lola, who suggested they do so, tries to make Granny a present on her own.

added.title: Tell-A-Photo
added.description: As Granny assembles her photo album, the babies gather around to reminisce about all the happy times they've spent together.

removed.title: The Trouble with Larry
removed.description: Petunia invents an imaginary friend to help her always get her way.

removed.title: An UnbeLEAFable Day
removed.description: While the trains are setting up for the Vicarstown Fall Festival, Thomas is feeling down about the end of summer and the changing weather.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Magic Act
removed.description: Pocoyo is doing a magic show. He expects everyone to watch very carefully and take him very seriously but unfortunately his tricks don't quite go to plan and his friends all laugh. They're really enjoying the show. They think Pocoyo is great at being a funny magician. But that's not what Pocoyo wants to be - he wants to be taken very seriously - so he goes off in a huff. In the meantime, Pato, Elly and Baby Bird go around Pocoyo-land to tell everyone about the magnificent hilarious magician whose show they enjoy so much. As Pocoyo sulks, his friends gather around him, excited to see his tricks. Pocoyo is overwhelmed that his friends liked his show so much. He does some more tricks and his friends are thrilled.

removed.title: Melissa the Hero
removed.description: Melissa brags about helping Petunia to the point of self-aggrandizement.

removed.title: Ocean
removed.description: Blippi's trusty BlippiMobile safely transports him to a whole new underwater world! He dives into the sea, where he gets an ocean tour from a local resident, Jerry the Jellyfish. They swim through a huge kelp forest, explore the ocean floor and meet interesting underwater creatures along the way!

removed.title: Cool for Cats
removed.description: Sylvester believes a commercial that says eating Chewy Chomps will make him cool.

removed.title: Too Hot to Handle/The Big Squeak/Big Jumping Spider
removed.description: Findley can't resist some freshly baked cookies that are too hot to eat./ Avocado's new toy is driving everyone crazy with its noisy squeaker./ Lucas performs epic jumps all around House./ Findley is nervous and wishes Lucas wouldn't jump.

removed.title: Accidents Happen Boo Boo Song
removed.description: Ella falls over, but Heidi the Horse teaches her to get right back up again!

removed.title: Eggy Head
removed.description: Bing and his friends are at Amma's creche today making Eggy Heads! Amma explains that Eggy Heads need 7 sleeps, water, light and patience to grow it's cress hair. But Bing has an idea to help his Eggy grow cress hair quicker...

removed.title: Getting Truffy with It
removed.description: Truff is happy. He has found a necklace that makes him even Truffier! Except he had no idea the necklace belongs to Starmush. And the Mushelder promised there will be consequences for whoever took it. Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit now have to save Truff from being consequenced.

removed.title: Lightning Bark
removed.description: Fung and Miff have come across a rare piece of bark struck by lightning. Chep desperately wants to add it to his collection, but Fung and Miff have no intention to give it to him. Now remembering every time Chep has been nice to them, Fung and Miff end up doing something they never thought possible…

removed.title: Some Luck
removed.description: While the Bears are transporting a Whiffle Wizard to a distant meadow, Good Luck seems to have a run of bad luck. His belief in his own bad fortune causes him to lose confidence, causing ever more "bad luck." It's only when he understands that we make our own luck that his "luck" changes.

removed.title: Bath Song
removed.description: Ella gets covered in mud so she goes into Mei's farmhouse to have a bath.

removed.title: Pocoyo's Puppet Show
removed.description: Pocoyo finds a puppet theatre and some puppets. Brilliant! Time for him to be a puppeteer. He puts on a show for Caterpillar and Baby Bird. They love it, especially when the puppets do funny things like fall over. They bring Pato and Elly along to watch the show too. When Pocoyo makes fun of Pato and Elly with the puppets, Pato and Elly are nonplussed. They don't think it's so great to laugh at people. Pocoyo realizes that his show has upset his friends. He says sorry and explains he didn't mean it. Everyone makes friends again!

removed.title: In Bugs We Trust
removed.description: Bugs uses the babies' money to buy different toys than he promised.

removed.title: Lunch
removed.description: Bing and Sula are chefs today and helping Amma and Flop make lunch. It's Sula's favourite - Easy Peasy Pasta! But, what happens when lunch is served and Bing sees all the ingredients mixed up together?

removed.title: Honey
removed.description: Blippi and FETCH shrink down and fly inside a very active beehive, where they meet Bijon, the fast-talking, fast-moving Worker Bee. With a talent for rhyming and making honey, Bijon rhymes her way through the sweet explanation of how delicious honey is made. What a very buzzy... erm...busy day!

removed.title: Ghost Camp/Boo/Never Boop a Robot
removed.description: When Lucas and friends go camping, Avocado tells a scary story. Lucas now thinks there's a ghost in the garden./ Lucas loves to give his friends a scare on Halloween./ When Lucas boops a robot, he and his friends are chased around House!

removed.title: Mine
removed.description: Bing and Pando are on their way home from the beach! And when Pando goes back to Bing's house to collect Bullabaloo, they decide to play one last game before bedtime - Hide and Seek. But where will Pando hide?

removed.title: The Need for Feed/The Zipline Sisters of Treetop Woods
removed.description: MacBarm is bringing food to his hungry chickens, that is, until all of the food falls out of his truck./Grandma and her twin sister want to recreate their old zipline act, but quickly discover that the zipline no longer exists!

removed.title: The Littlest Tweety
removed.description: Tweety is tired of being overlooked because of his diminutive size.

removed.title: Picnic Puzzle
removed.description: Pocoyo and Elly have organized a picnic and they leave Pato in charge of guarding the sandwiches while they get everything ready. Incredibly the sandwiches suddenly start moving around. Pato can't believe his eyes. When Pocoyo and Elly return they are angry with Pato. They think he took the sandwiches himself. They give him one more chance, leaving him in charge of guarding the cake. Once again, amazingly, the cake runs away apparently on its own. Pato is once again berated by Pocoyo and Elly until they see what's going on with their own eyes. Pocoyo investigates further and discovers who it is that's moving the food around: ANTS! Having worked out what's going on, the friends invite the ants along to the picnic and they all have fun together.

removed.title: Baby Bird Sitting
removed.description: When Sleepy Bird has to pop out for a while, she needs someone to look after little Baby Bird. Pato volunteers because he thinks that's going to be a much easier job than tidying up the mess he's made with Pocoyo. Baby Bird, and his chum Caterpillar, run rings round Pato who eventually appeals to Pocoyo for help. Pocoyo thinks he can take care of the situation easily himself, but he similarly is foxed by the little tykes. Finally Pocoyo and Pato work out that in order to get the little ones to do what they want, they are going to need to collaborate. By the time Sleepy Bird returns, Baby Bird and Caterpillar are fast asleep. Little does Sleepy Bird know the chaos that got them to that point!

removed.title: Woof
removed.description: Bing and Flop are in the park, when a doggie called Sunshine comes to play catch with them! Bing loves playing with Sunshine, but what will happen when Bing realises he can't keep Sunshine?

removed.title: Valley of the Shamrocks
removed.description: When Grumpy replaces mission navigator Good Luck with a computerized navigational gadget, Good Luck feels useless -- until he saves the Valley of the Shamrocks and is proclaimed a hero by the Whiffles, who don't want him to leave. He is torn between staying with the Whiffles and remaining with the Bears.

removed.title: Everyone's Present
removed.description: Wow… Presents! One for Pocoyo, one for Elly and one for Pato! How exciting. Pocoyo's present is some string, Pato gets some paper and Elly some sticks. They have fun for a while, each playing with their own present in a bid to prove that it's the best of the bunch. But ultimately the friends get a little bored with their respective gifts. After all, there's only so much you can do with one thing. In a huff, the friends throw their new toys on the floor. And this is when they see the potential of the presents: they can combine them. They put the presents together to make a kite. Wonderful, something they can all play with together.

removed.title: Not Yours
removed.description: Bing's helping Flop pick up groceries in Padget's shop today. And while Flop is paying, Bing picks up a lolly and puts it in his pocket. But what happens when Flop explains to Bing that he has stolen the lolly?

removed.title: That's the Way the Windmill Blows!/Mecha Machine Makers!
removed.description: The windmill isn't turning, which means Sunny Field Farm has no power. The windmill needs to turn again so Zee can launch his rocket!/Izzy and Timmy are making a bird caller for Grandma, but have trouble connecting pieces of their machine.

removed.title: Ghost Train
removed.description: Percy has to deliver the mail on Halloween when everyone knows the legendary Ghost Train comes out! Thomas rolls along to help Percy face his fears, but when a "real" Ghost Train appears... things get almost spooky.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: They Sent Us a Pie/Dust in the Wind
removed.description: A giant pie is sent to Pretty Big City to stop an asteroid… but the Mechas and friends have eaten the whole thing!/The Singing Stone Heads are ready to perform at the Museum, but when they open their mouths, they sneeze instead of sing!

removed.title: Pull Together/Lift Up and Lift Off
removed.description: Ranger Nat is stuck at the bottom of the crevice, but the problem grows when Mecha Abby also gets stuck./Zee is ready to launch his rocket into space, but when the launchpad breaks, the rocket is launched into the farm instead.
